-- Peru Stocks: Candente Copper, Pomalca, Rio Alto, Sulliden
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-07-12T21:15:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-12/peru-stocks-candente-copper-pomalca-rio-alto-sulliden.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Peru trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the close of trade in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a seventh session, losing
0.7 percent to 19,954.85. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid
0.8 percent to 2,668.31.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, fell 3.8 percent to 50 centimos after sugar declined
in  New York , said Edwin Paz, a Lima-based trader with Provalor
SAB.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner,
dropped for a fourth day, losing 1.9 percent to $4.07 after gold
slumped to a two-week low in New York.  Sulliden Gold Corp Ltd. (SUE)  , a gold exploration
company, declined 1.9 percent to $1.02.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, fell 1.8 percent to 53 cents after copper dropped in
New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
